library(readr)
data_final <- read_csv("MA_Public_Schools_2017.csv")
## Rows: 1861 Columns: 302
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (18): School Code, School Name, School Type, Function, Contact Name, Ad...
## dbl (278): Zip, PK_Enrollment, K_Enrollment, 1_Enrollment, 2_Enrollment, 3_E...
## num   (2): AP_Test Takers, AP_Tests Taken
## lgl   (4): MCAS_3rdGrade_Math_SGP, MCAS_3rdGrade_Math_Incl. in SGP(#), MCAS_...
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
data_highschool <- data_final |>
  filter(`12_Enrollment` >= 1 | `11_Enrollment` >= 1 | `10_Enrollment` >= 1 | `9_Enrollment` >= 1)
library(ggplot2)

data_highschool <- data_highschool |>
  mutate(Total_SAT = `Average SAT_Reading` + `Average SAT_Writing` + `Average SAT_Math`)
ggplot(data = data_highschool,
       mapping = aes(x = `Average In-District Expenditures per Pupil`,
                     y = Total_SAT)) +
  geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 103 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 103 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

ggplot(data = data_highschool,
       mapping = aes(x = `Salary Totals`,
                     y = Total_SAT/100)) +
  geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  scale_x_log10()
